<br>
Quintessence = 105pp<br>
<br>
Shaman Gate potion = 168pp<br>
<br>
Both are absolute minimum costs to make not factoring in fail rates.<br>
<br>
Quint is trivial somewhere under 35. Most Shaman have sufficient skill to make this reliably.<br>
<br>
Gate potions trivial at 170 - skill not obtainable to a sSaman lower than level 58, and only a small minority of Shaman bother to get skill that high. Most stop well before they reach 100 (50 or so is enough to get minimum fail rate on SoW potions).<br>
<br>
<br>
In summary : Quintessence is cheaper and arguably far easier to aquire. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">Zyphyr Runnersbane</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
